This paper is a review on learning with deep generative models, which is a highly-active area in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper discusses different learning algorithms and future research directions, which are topics that are commonly discussed in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SD). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
